# Preserve the existing production URL for Flow A (the control)
# so Google Ads URLs don't break. Status 200 is a rewrite (URL stays
# the same in the browser); the folder name is dev-only.
#
# The first rule catches the no-slash form so Pages' built-in
# slash-normalization redirect (which drops the query string) never
# fires — that redirect was stripping UTMs from Google Ads clicks
# whose Final URL resolved to /massage-therapy-calgary (no slash).
/massage-therapy-calgary    /massage-therapy-calgary-flow-a/  200
/massage-therapy-calgary/*  /massage-therapy-calgary-flow-a/:splat  200
